comment: Coffee is good, but after the Corona epidemic, there is a problem with accumulating points to upgrade members to Platinum. At first I didn't pay attention, but when I finished my first drink, when I printed out the bill, I saw it was 289 points. A while later, my friend came over so I ordered 2 more portions of beef rice and 1 cup of coffee. When I paid, I didn't pay attention to the points, but when I got home, I saw that there were 284 points left. The next time I drink coffee, it's still 280. I wonder if the shops will tell me to contact IT. My next drinking spot is 3/2, DBP, CMT8, LTK. So my score goes up, but it's like if I drink at that place regularly 2 or 3 times, my score goes down again. Most recently, my score went back up to 292 points, but on the 28th or 29th, when I drank coffee at 5:00 p.m. at Ly T. Kiet's restaurant, my score was deducted again to 288 points (this score is a promotion score, not a deduction when pay). Or Trung Nguyen changed its policy of not wanting to promote Platinum status or there were negative problems in Trung Nguyen's franchised coffee shops. Please ask Trung Nguyen to review my case. If you want evidence, please contact me for specific work. I also wondered about this at 3/2 and DBP shops but it still didn't work. For other customers whose membership cards are about to be upgraded, please check them out.
